<subSubSection id="C36F0AA4FF8ECC49A38CBE6AFB79F862" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCA592FFF8ECC49A38CBE6AFB79F862" blockId="24.[151,1437,1677,1992]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">
<emphasis id="B901853DFF8ECC49A38CBE6AFEFCF892" bold="true" box="[199,314,1821,1847]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFF8ECC49A2F3BE6AFC95F892" authority="Kriechbaumer, 1879" authorityName="Kriechbaumer" authorityYear="1879" box="[440,851,1821,1847]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis id="B901853DFF8ECC49A2F3BE6AFDACF892" box="[440,618,1821,1847]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">Ophion minutus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE424DEFF8ECC49A125BE6AFC95F892" author="Kriechbaumer, J." box="[622,851,1821,1847]" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" pagination="105 - 106" refId="ref32407" refString="Kriechbaumer, J. (1879) Ophion minutus n. sp. Entomologische Nachrichten, 5, 105 - 106." type="journal article" year="1879">Kriechbaumer, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but usually with less pale markings on the mesosoma and on average slightly larger. The temples and the face is narrower and the flagellomeres are longer. In all known specimens, the posterior transverse carina is complete, m-shaped, while it usually is partly or completely missing in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFF8ECC49A3DCBEFEFE8DF806" authorityName="Kriechbaumer" authorityYear="1879" box="[151,331,1929,1955]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis id="B901853DFF8ECC49A3DCBEFEFE8DF806" box="[151,331,1929,1955]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">Ophion minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Also similar to the other three species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7522ACFF8ECC49A00CBEFDFC04F806" authorityName="Kriechbaumer" authorityYear="1879" box="[839,962,1930,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis id="B901853DFF8ECC49A00CBEFDFC04F806" box="[839,962,1930,1956]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="175">O. minutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
aggregate described in this study, but with more yellow pale markings, whitish on the other species, and with the face considerably wider.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF0A09A7FF8FCC48A3DCBE60FCB3F83E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225680" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5225680" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225680/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="176" startId="25.[151,250,1815,1839]" targetBox="[151,1436,181,1779]" targetPageId="25">
